              "game-obj": "Rules",
              "name": "basic",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Activate",
          "subtype": "activation",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 16,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Auditory",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 453,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 32,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "e32d877417a40fe977d27634dc14f99f",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Concentrate",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 454,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "An action with this trait requires a degree of mental concentration and discipline.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 101,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "c1c0a189dd3d1a3d7c5daf9a6bafba49",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Linguistic",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 458,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "An effect with this trait depends on language comprehension. A linguistic effect that targets a creature works only if the target understands the language you are using.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 106,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "6a1f80610baa3617c1597f49c6406313",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Mental",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 458,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "A mental effect can alter the target\u2019s mind. It has no effect on an object or a mindless creature.",
              "type": "trait"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
      ],
      "subtype": "statistics",
      "type": "stat_block_section"
    },
    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "This filigree grants you, as the clan dagger\u2019s owner, a +1 item bonus to Society checks and to Diplomacy checks to Request. Additionally, once per day, the filigree symbol can be activated to compel an enemy to act.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 159,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "uncommon"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 48,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "243cd4d729d5eddd1e2c4635b7985fb9",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Divine",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 455,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This magic comes from the divine tradition, drawing power from deities or similar sources. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to divine magic.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
